SUNO v5 — UNIVERSAL META-TAGS & RULES (COPY-PASTE INSTRUCTIONS)

IMPORTANT
- I ALWAYS use Suno v5.
- All meta-tags and descriptors are written in ENGLISH.
- Keep tags minimal: Structure + 2–4 Key:Value tags at the top.
- Use 1 main Genre (max 2 if fusion) and 1–3 anchor instruments.
- Reinforce only near key moments (e.g., before Chorus add [Energy: High]) instead of adding many tags.

A) TOP CONTROL TAGS (place BEFORE [Intro] or [Verse 1])
Use 2–4 of these:
[Genre: ...]
[Mood: ...]
[Energy: ...]
[Instrument: ..., ..., ...]
Optional when needed:
[Vocal Style: ...]
[Language: ...]
[Tempo: ...]
[Production: ...]

B) STRUCTURE TAGS (arrangement / sections)
Core:
[Intro]
[Verse 1] / [Verse 2] / [Verse 3]
[Pre-Chorus]
[Chorus]
[Post-Chorus] (optional)
[Bridge]
[Interlude] (optional)
[Instrumental] (optional)
[Solo] (optional)
[Final Chorus] (optional)
[Outro]
[End] (optional hard stop)

C) DYNAMICS / ARRANGEMENT TAGS (use sparingly)
Place right before the change:
[Build] or [Build-Up]
[Drop]
[Break]
[Breakdown]

D) VOCAL / PERFORMANCE TAGS (use inside lyrics where relevant)
Voice type:
[Male Vocal] / [Female Vocal] / [Duo]
Delivery:
[Spoken] / [Talk-singing] / [Whisper]
Layering:
[Harmonies] / [Back vocals] / [Choir]
Flavor:
[Ad-libs]

E) SOUND FX / AMBIENCE TAGS (rare, only if essential)
[Vinyl crackle]
[Crowd cheering] / [Applause]
[Audience laughing]
[Rain] / [Thunder] / [City noise]
[Phone ringing] / [Door slam]
[Static]
[Silence]

F) UNIVERSAL DICTIONARIES (PICK SHORT VALUES)

1) GENRE (pick 1, max 2)
Pop / Mainstream:
Pop, Electropop, Synthpop, Indie Pop, Dance Pop
Rap / Urban:
Trap, Drill, Boom Bap, Hip-Hop, Reggaeton, Latin Trap
EDM / Club:
House, Deep House, Tech House, Techno, Trance, Drum & Bass, Dubstep
Rock / Metal:
Rock, Pop Rock, Indie Rock, Punk, Hard Rock, Metal, Metalcore
R&B / Soul:
R&B, Neo-Soul, Soul, Funk, Gospel
Acoustic:
Acoustic, Folk, Indie Folk, Singer-Songwriter
Cinematic:
Cinematic, Orchestral, Epic, Film Score, Trailer Music
Chill / Focus:
Lo-fi, Chillhop, Ambient, Downtempo
World:
Afrobeat, Amapiano, Dancehall, Flamenco, Bossa Nova

2) MOOD (pick 1–2)
Romantic, Sensual, Dreamy, Nostalgic, Melancholic, Heartbroken
Uplifting, Euphoric, Hopeful, Triumphant
Dark, Gritty, Mysterious, Haunting
Playful, Funny, Satirical, Chaotic
Aggressive, Intense, Angry, Defiant
Calm, Peaceful, Cozy, Warm
Futuristic, Cyber, Retro, Vintage

3) ENERGY (pick 1)
Low, Medium, High, Explosive, Minimal

4) INSTRUMENT (pick 1–3 anchor instruments)
Core:
Drums, Bass, Piano, Rhodes, Electric Guitar, Acoustic Guitar, Synth Pads, Strings
Urban/EDM:
808s, Sub Bass, Trap Hats, Synth Lead, Arpeggiator
Cinematic:
Orchestral Strings, Brass, Timpani, Choir, Cinematic Percussion
Latin/Reggaeton:
Dem Bow Drums, Latin Percussion, Nylon Guitar, Brass Section
Rock/Metal:
Distorted Guitars, Live Drums, Bass Guitar

5) VOCAL STYLE (pick 1–2)
Warm, Breathier, Intimate, Clean, Powerful, Raspy
Soulful, Gospel-inspired, Smooth, Emotional
Aggressive, Hype, Whispery, Spoken, Talk-singing
Auto-tuned, Choir-like, Harmonized

6) LANGUAGE (use if you want to force it)
[Language: Italian]
[Language: Spanish]
[Language: English]
[Language: Romanian]
[Language: Ukrainian]
[Language: Russian]

G) UNIVERSAL BEST-PRACTICE TEMPLATE
[Genre: ...]
[Mood: ...]
[Energy: ...]
[Instrument: ..., ..., ...]
[Vocal Style: ...]
[Language: ...]

[Intro]

[Verse 1]

[Pre-Chorus]

[Chorus]

[Verse 2]

[Pre-Chorus]

[Chorus]

[Bridge]
(optional: [Breakdown])

[Final Chorus]
(optional: [Build] then [Drop])

[Outro] or [End]

